                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page,
                           alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each subsection of the
                           text; elements of punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some
                           words like kǝfl (e.g., fols. 9ra, 13rb, 24ra), fǝkkāre (e.g., fols.
                           121rb, 121va, 122ra), rabǝʿ (e.g., fols.122vc, 124rb, 126va), yǝbe (e.g.,
                           fols. 130ra, 130va), tǝʿǝzaz (e.g., fols. 132vc, 133ra).</seg>
